profile_positions.description:
• Coordinated all audience relations and ensured satisfactory service delivery;
• Kept updated database of existing target audience and maintained a periodic reporting system;
• Provided adequate analysis report on target audience;
• Responsible for providing inputs and developing zone-specific content for the design, development, and management of public awareness communications programs;
• Monitored all aspects of the communications and maintained a periodic reporting system;
• Provided creative and collaborative, as well as encouraged a transparent environment where I informed everyone about project developments;
• Responsible for organizing program activities, including assessments,
workshops, meetings, and attending meetings when necessary;
• Maintained detailed records of program activities and files and updated the management periodically.

•	Provided inputs and developed state-specific content for the design, development, and management of public awareness communications programs;
•	Provided remote monitoring of the event;
•	Produced all email campaigns, solicited content from internal sources, and managed reviews, testing, and sending;
•	Remotely coordinated logistics of team leads in 7 states concurrently;
•	Monitored workshops and conferences and developed excerpts from each for weekly social media updates.

•Led negotiations for existing and new partnerships;
•Identified with key stakeholders in the industry and developed strategies for stakeholder engagement;
•Reviewed policies and led awareness creation for the organization;
•Carried out researches towards new prospects and developed strategies for engagement and follow up;
•Developed RFPs and followed up with process till approved;
•Took part in drafting and follow up of 2 grants proposals for 2 NGOs till approval;
•Successfully managed 2 grants for organizations;
•Documented all processes for accountability and knowledge sharing.

•	Led a team of 5 ladies from the mentorship program to start and design project;
•	Led the community engagements for the project;
•	Coordinated and supported communications projects, outreach, and products as required;
•	Developed advocacy and strategic communications plan;
•	Captured and documented information during community engagements;
•	Raise funds for the project through the deployment of digital media skills and well-meaning friends;
•	Developed final project report

•	Supported the preparation and presentation to USAID of reports and written communications on the progress and impact of program activities;
•	Sourced contents for the production of reports for internal and external audiences and weekly summaries for all staff on what is happening across the project in the states;
•	Responsible for note-taking, development, and documentation of information from KII and FGD meetings for information gathering;
•	Conducted desk review for the project, documented and disseminated information for learning and knowledge management;
•	Developed a comprehensive report based on information from all engagements and shared the same with senior managers.

• Established and maintained the system for monitoring the progress of the project;
• Developed and maintained a weekly schedule for the Communications Team;
• Developed and executed social and print media campaigns for key days, themes, and priority for upcoming content;
• Carried out social media analysis of message reach and shared periodically for project monitoring;
• Organized planning twice each week for smooth operations and to monitor implementation;
• Promoted new contents, key pages, and calls-to-action across channels;
• Coordinated periodic project reporting and documentation for each stage of the project and shared with the project team.

•	Facilitated series of workshops on Water Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH);
•	Delivered periodic Training of Trainers workshops;
•	Coordinated baseline survey for UNICEF in four different states;
•	Trained and recruited over 40 Enumerators for the exercise;
•	Organized and led planning meetings with members of the project stakeholders, LGA chairpersons, State RUWASSA and various key staff;
•	Planned and carried out advocacy visits to the communities involved for adequate sensitization towards planned projects.

•	Developed day-to-day project plan/strategy for implementation and advancement of the project;
•	Supported the team to implement the project and ensured consistency;
•	Managed and documented each process of the project for sharing, learning, and review;
•	Coordinated, as well as promoted dialogue and information exchanges between the organization and donor agencies and ensured the timeliness and quality of each report;
